tweet:
As the breakeven drifts down further toward 2%, I would expect the Fed to signal the end of this rate hike cycle.

This will happen faster than the market is currently anticipating. Below 2% we have the Spectre of Deflation, something the Fed can‚Äôt have.

name: Anthony Scaramucci
tweet: Declines below 2% are associated with crisis -- 2008, 2015, 2020 -- and have spurred the FED to adopt negative real rates to avert deflation, which laid the groundwork for this inflation shock.¬† They don't want that to happen again.

name: Anthony Scaramucci
tweet: 10 UST brkeven, which is the market's implied rate of inflation, is down to 2.36%, and falling.¬† 10 Yr is 3.69% and the 10 Yr TIP yield is 1.33%.¬† The difference (2.36%) is the implied expected rate of inflation.¬† The St. Louis Fed tracks this --¬†https://t.co/qxeeByqX51
